        <p>Juliet is used to being ignored. She's lived a life of solitude for centuries. When Romeo walks into her life, things start to change and she's able to feel again. But with that feeling comes a pain she's not ready to deal with. As mysterious events begin to unfold, she'll need to undertake a journey to uncover her past, so she can finally be able to stop her future.</p>
        <p>Romeo isn't quite sure what to make of Juliet. But when she is cast as the lead in the school play alongside him, unexplainable things start to happen. He's either going crazy, or her illogical rantings are actually true. And if that's the case, he'll have to fight the clock to save her from herself.</p>
